Save and share for your next booking! 

1. Free Trials Without Commitment
• Trials require time, products, and effort — they’re usually paid or adjusted in final booking.

2. Last-Minute Bookings Always Being Available
• Artists get booked in advance, especially during peak wedding season. Book early!

3. Miracle Results on Untreated Skin
• Great makeup starts with good skincare. Expect better results if your skin is prepped.

4. Unlimited Time
• Artists work on a schedule. Respect the time slot, as they may have back-to-back bookings.

5. Copy-Paste Celebrity Looks
• Every face is different — inspiration is welcome, but replication isn’t always possible (or ideal).

6.Makeup That Lasts 24+ Hours Without Touch-Ups
• Even the best products have limits. Touch-ups or setting sprays help, but nothing is forever.

7.Free Product Recommendations or Skincare Consultations
• That’s a separate service. General tips are fine, but deep skin consultations are for dermatologists or estheticians.

8. Refunds for Personal Change of Mind
• Once booked and blocked, that time can’t be rebooked — most artists have a clear cancellation policy.

9. Free “Touch-Ups” for Friends or Family
• One booking covers one person, unless stated otherwise. Friends need their own slots.

10. Unrealistic Before-After Expectations
• Filters and editing seen online can’t be recreated 100% in real life. Expect enhancement, not illusions.
